path: ./Audit_Reports_2024/Techrate/Little Bunny Rocket Full Smart Contract Security Audit.pdf

findings.title: Owner can change tax and liquidity fees
findings.description: The contract owner has the privilege to modify tax and liquidity fees.

findings.title: Owner can change maximum transaction amount
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to modify the maximum transaction amount, which could lead to potential security risks.

findings.title: Owner can exclude from the fee
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to exclude certain addresses or transactions from paying fees.

findings.title: Owner can change marketingDivisor
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to modify the marketing divisor, which could lead to unintended consequences.

findings.title: Owner can change minimum number of tokens to add to liquidity
findings.description: The contract owner has the privilege to modify the minimum number of tokens required to add liquidity.

findings.title: Owner can change buyBackUpperLimit
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to modify the buyBackUpperLimit, which could lead to unintended consequences.

findings.title: Owner can change marketing address
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to modify the marketing address, which could lead to potential security risks.

findings.title: Owner can manually buyback
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to manually buy back tokens, which could lead to potential security risks.

findings.title: Owner can send all contract BNB balance to marketing address
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to transfer the entire BNB balance of the contract to the marketing address.

findings.title: Owner can enable and disable buyBack
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to enable or disable the buyback feature.

findings.title: Owner can enable before and after presale modes
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to enable or disable presale modes, which could lead to potential security risks if not properly managed.

findings.title: Owner can lock and unlock
findings.description: The owner has the ability to lock and unlock, which could allow them to retake privileges even after ownership was renounced.
